; class-curriculum.fk — the mesh GRADUALLY grows how many classes it can detect ON DEVICE, ON METAL,
; taught by the REMOTE MIND and gated by CROSS-MESH STABILITY. The oracle-flywheel turned onto the
; CLASS VOCABULARY itself: the rented mind teaches FEWER classes over time as the device learns more
; natively. "The remote mind carries the syllabus; the cameras prove each lesson; a class joins the
; on-device vocabulary only once the mesh AGREES it has been learned."
;
; THE ARC (Urs). A remote-mind cell (remote-mind-sensors.fk — mind-rich, sensor-poor) has no eyes or
; ears, but it KNOWS the taxonomy: how many classes exist and what they are called (the syllabus). The
; device cells have the metal — real cameras, real mics — but start blank: zero classes detectable.
; The remote mind TEACHES one class at a time by labelling exemplars the device captured on real frames;
; the device ENROLLS the class (sound-classify's sc-enroll, generalized kind-agnostic); but a class only
; JOINS the on-device vocabulary once the CAMERAS CROSS-MESH AGREE on it — the same cross-witness
; confidence the mesh already produces for free, gated by the champion-challenger PROVEN window. The
; count grows MONOTONICALLY: adding a class never forgets the prior ones (no catastrophic forgetting — a
; re-encounter of an old class still classifies). An unknown region escalates back to the remote mind —
; the next lesson the flywheel feeds.
;
; THE ONE ENGINE — kind as DATA. The SAME curriculum grows the stable vocabulary for OBJECTS, SOUNDS,
; and PRESENCES. A class is (kind label exemplar) — the kind word ("object" / "sound" / "presence") is a
; FIELD on the row, never three recipes. "chair" (object) and "birdsong" (sound) enroll, stabilize, and
; classify through the IDENTICAL walk; only the kind-field differs. This mirrors how sc-enroll already
; enrolls a NEW class and how world-model.fk carries kind on the entity row — we generalize that one
; pattern, we do not fork it. The classifier itself is sound-classify's nearest-exemplar by cosine
; (se-dot), kind-agnostic by construction.
;
; COMPOSED, never re-derived:
;   sound-classify.fk        sc-enroll — the ENROLL-a-new-class pattern (add (label features) to a
;                            roster); generalized here to (kind label features). se-nearest / se-dot is
;                            the nearest-exemplar classifier the detect step routes on.
;   cross-witness-economy.fk cwe-confidence / cwe-spend-oracle? — the cross-mesh AGREEMENT = the
;                            STABILITY signal. When N independent cameras agree on a class their summed
;                            trust is high; that high agreement IS the proof the class has been learned.
;                            An unknown region is the low-agreement frontier that escalates to the mind.
;   champion-challenger.fk   cc-promote? — earned authority over a WINDOW: a class is stable only when
;                            the cross-mesh agreement holds over a long-enough window (never one frame's
;                            say). The promotion gate. (prefix ccur- — NOT cc-, no clash.)
;   remote-mind-sensors.fk   the remote mind as TEACHER — its labels are the syllabus; rms-sensor-names
;                            shape names what a bodiless mind carries (here: the taxonomy it teaches).
;   world-model.fk           wm-* — where the classified entities live; a stable class is what the world
;                            model can now name on its own, off the oracle.
;
; A CLASS row is (kind label exemplar):
;   kind      "object" / "sound" / "presence" — DATA, the only thing that differs across the three.
;   label     the class name the remote mind taught (the syllabus entry) — "chair", "birdsong", ...
;   exemplar  a quantized feature vector (sc-features' sound-print / an embedding) — the recognition
;             signal the nearest-exemplar classifier matches over. Kind-agnostic: object texture today,
;             sound-print tomorrow, the dot is the same.
;
; All integer/string/list on the surface, so every row crosses all four kernels deterministically. The
; embeddings ride the carrier's organs exactly as sound-classify and identity-match do; the curriculum
; DECISION — what is in the stable vocabulary, is a class stable, does a region escalate — is the body's.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/speaker-embed.fk form-stdlib/sound-classify.fk form-stdlib/champion-challenger.fk form-stdlib/confidence-weighted-vote.fk form-stdlib/colearning-retire.fk form-stdlib/cross-witness-economy.fk
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/class-curriculum-band.fk (four-way at validate.sh, incl. fkwu)

(do
    ; ── A CLASS row (kind as DATA — the only per-kind difference) ──────────────────────────────────
    (defn ccur-class (kind label exemplar) (list kind label exemplar))
    (defn ccur-class-kind     (c) (nth c 0))
    (defn ccur-class-label    (c) (nth c 1))
    (defn ccur-class-exemplar (c) (nth c 2))

    ; ── ccur-syllabus: the ordered classes the remote mind KNOWS to teach — how many there are to
    ;    classify, and their labels. The remote mind (mind-rich, sensor-poor) carries the taxonomy; the
    ;    syllabus IS that taxonomy as the ordered class rows. The labels are the lessons; the device
    ;    learns them one at a time. taxonomy is a list of (kind label exemplar) the mind holds. ──
    (defn ccur-syllabus (taxonomy) taxonomy)
    ; how many classes the syllabus still holds to teach — the count the flywheel drives DOWN as the
    ; device learns more natively (the remote mind teaches FEWER over time).
    (defn ccur-syllabus-count (taxonomy) (len taxonomy))
    ; the labels the syllabus carries — what the mind can name (its sparse taxonomy roster).
    (defn ccur-syllabus-labels (taxonomy)
        (if (eq (len taxonomy) 0) (empty)
            (cons (ccur-class-label (head taxonomy))
                  (ccur-syllabus-labels (tail taxonomy)))))

    ; ── ccur-enroll: enroll a NEW class from remote-mind-labelled exemplars — the sc-enroll
    ;    GENERALIZATION, kind as DATA. sc-enroll adds (label features) to a roster; we add
    ;    (kind label exemplar), so the SAME enroll grows the OBJECT, SOUND, or PRESENCE roster — the kind
    ;    is a field, not a branch. The label came from the remote mind (the syllabus); the exemplar was
    ;    captured on a real device frame. This is enrollment off any oracle: the recognition stays HERE,
    ;    the label only seeds the roster. ──
    (defn ccur-enroll (vocab kind label exemplar)
        (cons (ccur-class kind label exemplar) vocab))

    ; ── ccur-stable?: is the class CROSS-MESH stable — the PROMOTION GATE. The cameras/cells produce
    ;    witness ballots (label weight) for the class; cross-witness confidence (cwe-confidence, the SAME
    ;    summed-trust fusion the mesh routes on) measures their AGREEMENT. High agreement over a
    ;    long-enough WINDOW is the proof the class is learned — exactly cc-promote?'s earned-authority
    ;    shape: the cross-mesh history is the head-to-head window, min-samples the trust floor, margin the
    ;    slack. A class is stable iff (a) the cross-mesh confidence clears the floor (cwe is NOT spending
    ;    the oracle — the mesh already agrees) AND (b) the agreement holds over the proven window. Never
    ;    one frame's say; the cameras must AGREE, over time. ──
    ;   witnesses : (history candidates floor min-samples margin) — the cross-mesh evidence for the class:
    ;     history    the cross-mesh agreement window (each trial (oracle-correct native-correct))
    ;     ballots    the per-camera (label weight) votes for THIS class
    ;     candidates the labels the ballots range over (for cwe-confidence's fusion)
    ;     floor      the cross-witness confidence floor (agreement must clear it — else the oracle spends)
    ;     min-samples / margin  the champion-challenger proven-window gate
    (defn ccur-stable-history    (w) (nth w 0))
    (defn ccur-stable-ballots    (w) (nth w 1))
    (defn ccur-stable-candidates (w) (nth w 2))
    (defn ccur-stable-floor      (w) (nth w 3))
    (defn ccur-stable-min        (w) (nth w 4))
    (defn ccur-stable-margin     (w) (nth w 5))

    (defn ccur-stable? (class witnesses)
        (do
            (let conf  (cwe-confidence (ccur-stable-ballots witnesses)
                                       (ccur-stable-candidates witnesses)))
            ; the mesh AGREES (cross-witness confidence clears the floor — cwe self-labels, no oracle
            ; spend) AND the agreement is PROVEN over the champion-challenger window.
            (if (and (eq (cwe-self-label? conf (ccur-stable-floor witnesses)) 1)
                     (eq (cc-promote? (ccur-stable-history witnesses)
                                      (ccur-stable-min witnesses)
                                      (ccur-stable-margin witnesses)) 1)) 1 0)))

    ; ── ccur-vocab membership: is a label already in the on-device vocabulary? The monotonic guard reads
    ;    it — a class already learned is never re-added (and never forgotten). ──
    (defn ccur-has? (vocab label)
        (if (eq (len vocab) 0) 0
            (if (str_eq (ccur-class-label (head vocab)) label) 1
                (ccur-has? (tail vocab) label))))

    ; ── ccur-grow: add a STABLE class to the on-device vocabulary, MONOTONIC. A new stable class is
    ;    CONSED on; prior classes are conserved unchanged (no catastrophic forgetting — every old class
    ;    still classifies). If the label is ALREADY in the vocabulary the vocab is returned unchanged (a
    ;    re-teach never duplicates and never forgets). Growth only ever ADDS. ──
    (defn ccur-grow (vocab class)
        (if (eq (ccur-has? vocab (ccur-class-label class)) 1)
            vocab
            (cons class vocab)))

    ; ── ccur-count: how many classes the device detects stably NOW — the growing number. The count the
    ;    flywheel drives UP (more native classes) as the syllabus count falls (fewer oracle lessons). ──
    (defn ccur-count (vocab) (len vocab))

    ; ── ccur-detect: classify a region into the STABLE vocabulary by nearest-exemplar (sound-classify's
    ;    se-nearest / se-dot decision, kind-AGNOSTIC), OR "unknown" -> escalate to the remote mind (the
    ;    next lesson the flywheel feeds). The vocab carries (kind label exemplar) rows; we match the
    ;    region's feature vector against the exemplars, return the nearest class's label if it clears the
    ;    floor, else "unknown". The kind rides along on the matched row (one engine over all kinds). ──
    ;   The roster for se-nearest is (label exemplar) — project the (kind label exemplar) rows down to it.
    (defn ccur-roster (vocab)
        (if (eq (len vocab) 0) (empty)
            (cons (list (ccur-class-label (head vocab)) (ccur-class-exemplar (head vocab)))
                  (ccur-roster (tail vocab)))))

    (defn ccur-detect (region vocab floor)
        (if (eq (len vocab) 0) "unknown"
            (do
                (let roster (ccur-roster vocab))
                (if (ge (se-sim region roster) floor)
                    (nth (se-nearest region roster) 0)
                    "unknown"))))

    ; did the region land in the stable vocabulary (1) or escalate to the remote mind (0)? The escalate
    ; coin — an "unknown" is the low-agreement frontier cross-witness-economy spends the oracle on.
    (defn ccur-known? (region vocab floor)
        (if (str_eq (ccur-detect region vocab floor) "unknown") 0 1))
    (defn ccur-escalate? (region vocab floor)
        (if (eq (ccur-known? region vocab floor) 1) 0 1))

    0)
